CREATE TABLE sensor_data (data_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, timestamp TIMESTAMP, value FLOAT, FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES sensors(sensor_id));</t><s>INSERT INTO sensors (sensor_id, sensor_name, location, timestamp, value) SELECT 5, 'Sensor5', 'Location5', '2021-01-05 00:00:00', 50.5;</s>

CREATE TABLE alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, timestamp TIMESTAMP, alert_message VARCHAR(255), FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES sensors(sensor_id));</t><s>insert into alerts (alert_id, sensor_id, timestamp, alert_message) select 2, 2, '2021-01-02 02:00:00', 'alert message 2';</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE sensors (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_name VARCHAR(50), location VARCHAR(50), timestamp TIMESTAMP, value FLOAT);

CREATE TABLE alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, timestamp TIMESTAMP, alert_message VARCHAR(255), FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES sensors(sensor_id));

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (data_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, timestamp TIMESTAMP, value FLOAT, FOREIGN KEY (sensor_id) REFERENCES sensors(sensor_id));

CREATE TABLE locations (location_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location_name VARCHAR(50));</t><s>INSERT INTO alerts (alert_id, sensor_id, timestamp, alert_message) SELECT 3, 3, '2021-01-03 02:00:00', 'Alert Message 3';</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))</t><s>INSERT INTO sensor_data (sensor_id, value, timestamp) SELECT sensor_id, RAND(), NOW() FROM sensor_location</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_status (status_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, is_active BOOLEAN)

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, value FLOAT, timestamp TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))</t><s>INSERT INTO sensor_data (sensor_id, value, timestamp) SELECT sensor_id, RAND(), NOW() FROM sensor_type</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, value FLOAT, timestamp TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)</t><s>INSERT INTO sensor_data (sensor_id, value, timestamp) SELECT sensor_id, RAND(), NOW() FROM sensor_alerts</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, value FLOAT, timestamp TIMESTAMP)</t><s>insert into sensor_data (sensor_id, value, timestamp) select sensor_id, rand(), now() from sensor_status</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE sensor_data (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, value FLOAT, timestamp TIMESTAMP)

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_status (status_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, is_active BOOLEAN)</t><s>INSERT INTO sensor_location (sensor_id, location) SELECT type_id, CONCAT('Location', type_id) FROM sensor_type</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))</t><s>insert into sensor_location (sensor_id, location) select sensor_id, concat('location', sensor_id) from sensor_alerts</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_status (status_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, is_active BOOLEAN)

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)</t><s>insert into sensor_location (sensor_id, location) select sensor_id, concat('location', sensor_id) from sensor_status</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_status (status_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, is_active BOOLEAN)

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))</t><s>insert into sensor_type (type_id, type_name) select sensor_id, concat('type', sensor_id) from sensor_status</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))</t><s>insert into sensor_type (type_id, type_name) select sensor_id, concat('type', sensor_id) from sensor_status</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)</t><s>INSERT INTO sensor_alerts (alert_id, sensor_id, alert_message) SELECT sensor_id, sensor_id, CONCAT('Alert message for sensor', sensor_id) FROM sensor_location</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_alerts (alert_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, alert_message TEXT)</t><s>insert into sensor_alerts (alert_id, sensor_id, alert_message) select sensor_id, sensor_id, concat('alert message for sensor', sensor_id) from sensor_type</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_status (status_id INT PRIMARY KEY, sensor_id INT, is_active BOOLEAN)</t><s>INSERT INTO sensor_status (status_id, sensor_id, is_active) SELECT sensor_id, sensor_id, RAND() > 0.5 FROM sensor_data</s>

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_type (type_id INT PRIMARY KEY, type_name VARCHAR(255))

CREATE TABLE sensor_location (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255))
